CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 23, 1939, pg. 9 reads: " "Happily Ever After" - Highlight in news last week in Duquesne, Pa., was the marriage of Johnnie Bell Lewis, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. John Lewis Sr., to Robert Leonard.  The Rev. J.O. Edwards who read the single ring ceremony at the Patterson street home of the bride last Thursday night, prayed that the popular couple would "enjoy many years of happiness." - Photo by Harris."
TitMainTitle: Bride Johnnie Bell Lewis Leonard cutting cake at dining room table with men and women, including groom Robert Leonard seated on left, in interior
